│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ My previous attempts to fix the issue by modifying `SLPVectorizer.cpp` have failed. This suggests that the problematic transformation from `select` to a logical `or` might be happening │
│ before the SLP vectorizer even runs.                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A common optimization pass that runs before vectorization is `InstCombine`. Let's investigate if `InstCombine` performs the transformation `select i1 Cond, i1 true, i1 V` into `or i1   │
│ Cond, V`. This transformation is generally correct for boolean logic but, as we've seen, is incorrect with respect to LLVM's `poison` semantics.                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The relevant code for this would be in `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp`. If I find this transformation, I need to make it safer by adding a check for `poison`.   │
│ The transformation should only occur if the operand `V` (the false value of the select) is guaranteed not to be poison.                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The transformation in `InstCombineSelect.cpp` likely looks like this:                                                                                                                    │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ // select C, true, X -> C | X                                                                                                                                                            │
│ if (match(SI.getTrueValue(), m_One()))                                                                                                                                                   │
│   return Builder.CreateOr(SI.getCondition(), SI.getFalseValue());                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ To fix this, I will add a condition to check if the false value can be poison. The `isGuaranteedNotToBePoison` utility can be used here. The modified code should look like this:        │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ // select C, true, X -> C | X                                                                                                                                                            │
│ if (match(SI.getTrueValue(), m_One())) {                                                                                                                                                 │
│   if (isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(SI.getFalseValue()))                                                                                                                                     │
│     return Builder.CreateOr(SI.getCondition(), SI.getFalseValue());                                                                                                                      │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This change will prevent `InstCombine` from creating the `or` instruction when it's unsafe, thus preserving the `select` for the SLP vectorizer. The SLP vectorizer, without the         │
│ problematic `or` instruction, will not perform the incorrect vectorization.                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will use `sed` to apply this change to `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp`.                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/return Builder.CreateOr(SI.getCondition(), SI.getFalseValue());/if (isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(SI.getFalseValue()))\n    return Builder.CreateOr(SI.getCondition(),             │
│ SI.getFalseValue());/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                                                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
